The paper proposes a game-theoretic model to study resource allocation in wireless networks, which suggests that it could belong to the Game Theory (cs.GT) sub-category. The focus on power and rate control in wireless networks with QoS constraints suggests that it could also belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. The consideration of energy efficiency and the utility function used in the game suggests that it could belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The study of tradeoffs among throughput, delay, network capacity, and energy efficiency suggests that it could also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the mention of delay performance and delay profiles suggests that it could belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
